metadata.name: Prisoner
metadata.description:
The swallow flies in a circle, unable to get out of the dome of the mosque.

So a person is frequently in captivity of his life ideas, formed habits, traditions, cultural and religious attitudes.

It would seem so simple. It is enough to look carefully to the side, to look from a different angle - and another path will open for you.

But no, we give out reflex reactions. We walk in circles and continue to repeat the patterns of behavior that have been established in our minds.
